    "created_at": "2015-11-23T05:14:03Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-11-23T05:14:03Z",
    "body": "It sounds like what you're really asking for is \n- more aggressive inference of captures to enable \"move\" inference\n- hybrid by-value/by-ref capturing closures\n\nNote that the second bullet can be hacked as follows:\n\n``` rust\nlet to_cap_by_ref = 0;\nlet to_cap_by_val = 0;\n\nlet explicit_ref = &to_cap_by_ref;\nfoo.map(move |x| {\n    to_cap_by_val + *explicit_ref;\n});\n```\n\nInstead of closing over some variables by-reference, we're instead capturing references to those variables by-value.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
